cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and text classification.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper involves extracting information from text data.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a machine learning approach for identifying story attributes.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper involves using AI techniques for text classification.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of user reviews to complement the gold standard dataset, which could have implications for understanding how people perceive and interpret stories.
